"07/12/2021 03:18am","94.239.135.75","0","0033139780385","Yasmeenbah1@gmail.com","29051976","Célibataire","Hôtesse - Stewart Jet Privé","Candidature spontanee","Yasmina Gueznay 
Current place: Paris 

8 years experience in the field
hard worker 
Flexible & Patient
Well organized
Optimistic
Speaks French, English, Spanish, Arabic 



Dear Sir, Dear Madam,



I would like to introduce myself as an applicant to the position of Flight Attendant.
I worked as a teacher for 4 years in Paris and Bahrain. I substituted a Spanish teacher for a class of 32 at Lycée Montaigne Paris 16th to prepare them for their Bachelor degree.
My experience in teaching was at the beginning only with teenagers but I ended up with teaching English and French at elementary schools through songs games acting drama classes and sometimes even Art.
Then I switched to Personal Assistant in various areas.
As a highly motivated and organized Personal Assistant, I am convinced that I will be a good asset to your Family and a great help because I have a multicultural experience in Paris, London, Spain, and 3 countries of the Middle East (The Royal family of Bahrain of Saudi Arabia and Dubai).
Mainly, I worked in teaching, translation, events and aviation all my life.
All areas taught me to be flexible, to work at a fast pace and to think out of the box when needed.
In each situation my main objective is to make my VIP s children s life enjoyable  and comfortable.
During my studies, I had my first experience as a teacher at College JEAN-PERRIN and I was responsible for teaching and educating a class of 32 teenagers, delivering them Spanish lessons through daily activities using songs plays movies and books. 
I joined the following year the Catholic Institute to teach in private Schools Elementary and Secondary Schools. It was  a very pleasant experience because the little ones really have fun learning a new language and it was enjoyable for me and them.
They have the capacity to learn at a fast pace and they taught me love and patience above all.
I planned and organized school trips to London, Essex and Sussex with 4 other teachers and a total of 64 students.
We went rafting and delta planing in the Vosges region with a total of 44 students during winter.
During those educational trips you learn how to know them better and you become more than their teacher. You are the nanny, the teacher, the parent, the confident and the nurse at the same time.
This helped me to switch to Aviation.
I have been working in Aviation since 2006 until today. As a well dedicated Flight Attendant I gain self control, and I became a very high-energy and organized individual.
My responsibilities included : note taking, booking hotels, ordering fine-dining, scheduling, specific shopping for my VIP from amenities to home blankets to dishes or special magazines and books, ordering special vegan kids menus and entertainment, buying kids amenities and games. Shopping special blankets gadgets children coloring books, taking care of their laundry, putting them to bed, cleaning the cabin, ordering flower arrangements for special occasions...
As a lead flight attendant for his Majesty of Bahrain I worked with the whole family trying to be as discreet as I could. The children adopted me quite rapidly as I have the ability to listen to them and adopt a positive attitude. Sometimes for their security I need to take an assertive tone but always with a smile. I believe if you love kids and treat them as your own they will love you back. Once you managed to settle that nice atmosphere and above all they feel you trust them and you love them the rest comes naturally. 
I know how valuable a teacher can be and I really enjoyed the exchange and  how to deal with the situation in a professional manner. That s my utmost satisfaction and above all make my VIP happy and his family at the same time. 


Hope my profile will meet your requirements, I am a native French Speaker but I also speak English, Arabic and Spanish. I am prepared to exceed expectations in this role, and make  your life easier.
Thank you very much for your time and I look forward to meeting you to discuss the skills I can bring to your family.

Sincerely,
Yasmina Gueznay 



