Cordialement,
Sarah Venturi



Dear Sir/ Madam,

My name is Sarah, I am 32 years old and currently living in Singapore since 2014. Over the past 10 years, I have travelled, lived, and worked in France, Switzerland, Canada, Singapore and Asia Pacific gaining experience in administration and as Personal Assistant to Senior Managers and Chairman of International companies. I am comfortable working and communication in both French, my mother tongue, and English business environment.

I have been working as Personal Assistant for 6 years. At the moment, I am working for a Small and Medium Enterprise (SME) with 15 employees in Singapore and about thirty in the UK. In my current role as Personal Assistant to the Chairman, I act as the primary gateway between him and his team, ensuring that he can focus on the tasks that require his personal attention while minimizing the scope for distractions.

After all these years, I have come to love this profession for the incredible diversity of tasks every single day. I am known for being detail-oriented, a good listener, well-organised team player and able to take initiative. I always strive to meet the deadlines without compromising on the quality of work.

With these experiences under my belt, I am looking for an opportunity to take the next step in my career. I will be relocating back to France around mid-end of August.

Thank you for your time and consideration. I hope to be given the opportunity to discuss further my candidacy with you. 

Sincerely, 
Sarah Venturi.
