"07/20/2021 01:13am","94.66.56.7","0","0033625442602","magogaagnes@gmail.com","16.03.1973","En couple","Assistant personnel","1984 PA","Dear Ms Biswas,

My long experience as Personal assistant to the renowned fashion designer Olivier Theyskens provided me with the opportunity, throughout 15 years, to have numerous responsibilities, all implying to be reliable, service-minded, good at planning, organizing and to communicate with a strong sense of diplomacy and discretion. 
I was in charge of Olivier Theyskens’private and professional agendas and was acting as the main liaison between all service providers and Olivier Theyskens.
I am very much at ease with foreseeing, prioritizing, planning and adjusting actions according to contingencies, which are common in the luxury business. In charge of budgets for the various projects of the fashion house Olivier Theyskens, I was also responsible for paying benefits to employees, settle payments to suppliers and keep track on the cashflow. Reporting to management was part of my weekly routine.
I worked in Paris and New York, amongst international teams in fashion houses Rochas, Nina Ricci and Theory. 

I helped planning and organizing 21 fashion shows in Paris and New York, the launch of a press book, a photo book, about 12 photo shootings, several office and home moves in Paris and between New York and Paris.

Fashion has a non-disputed reputation of being driven by demanding creative personalities. My long experience in the high-end fashion industry has allowed me to develop my competencies and strengthen my professionalism, by learning how to judge a situation and unite the adequate resources to solve it, how to respect the key persons’ time and space and yet answer their demands in due time and format. 

Thank you for your time and consideration. 

Respectfully yours,

Agnès Magoga
