"07/28/2021 12:38am","94.239.135.75","0","‪+33 6 14 55 16 65‬","yYasmeenbah1@gmail.com","29/05/1976","Célibataire","Assistant personnel","1984 PA","Dear Sir, Dear Madam,



I would like to introduce myself as an applicant to the position of a Personal Assistant.
I worked as a teacher for 4 years in Paris and Bahrain. I substituted a Spanish teacher for a class of 32 at Lycée Montaigne Paris 16th to prepare them for their Bachelor degree.
My experience in teaching was at the beginning only with teenagers but I ended up with teaching English and French at elementary schools through songs games acting drama classes and sometimes even Art.
Then I switched to Personal Assistant in various areas.
As a highly motivated and organized Personal Assistant, I am convinced that I will be a good asset to your Organization  and a great help because I have a multicultural experience in Paris, London, Spain, and 3 countries of the Middle East (The Royal family of Bahrain, of Saudi Arabia and Dubai).
Mainly, I worked in teaching, translation, project management, aviation and NGO s all my life.
All areas taught me to be flexible, to work at a fast pace and to think out of the box when needed.
In each situation my main objective is to make my VIP s life enjoyable and easier.
During my studies, I had my first experience as a teacher at College JEAN-PERRIN and I was responsible for teaching and educating a class of 32 teenagers, delivering them Spanish lessons through daily activities using songs plays movies and books. 
I joined the following year the Catholic Institute to teach in private Schools Elementary and Secondary Schools. It was  a very pleasant experience because the little ones really have fun learning a new language and it was enjoyable for me and them.
They have the capacity to learn at a fast pace and they taught me love and patience above all.
I planned and organized school trips to London, Essex and Sussex with 4 other teachers and a total of 64 students.
I had the opportunity to Work for Fundeso Madrid NGO where we could build schools in deserted areas in Chile and Peru. I translated their website into French and English and was writing reports in Spanish on other projects in Spain and North Africa.
This position was ideal for me as I was still in education, translating so many paperwork and leading project at the same time. It taught me patience,to never give up and love for charity. I became more confident and organised.
I volunteered the whole year but it was one my best professional experience as we achieved so many impossible goals.

This helped me to switch to Aviation.
I have been working in Aviation since 2006 until today. As a well dedicated Flight Attendant I gain self control, and I became a very high-energy and organized individual.
My responsibilities included : note taking, booking hotels, ordering fine-dining, scheduling, specific shopping for my VIP from amenities to home blankets to dishes or special magazines and books, ordering special vegan kids menus and entertainment, buying kids amenities and games. Shopping special blankets gadgets children coloring books, taking care of their laundry, putting them to bed, cleaning the cabin, ordering flower arrangements for special occasions...
As a lead flight attendant for his Majesty of Bahrain I worked with the whole family trying to be as discreet as I could. 
I believe an experience like yours will teach so much more it would be a dream come true.

I know how valuable a Personal Assistant  can be and I really enjoyed the flexibility and  how to deal with the situation in a professional manner. That s my utmost satisfaction and above all organise their schedule and help them achieve their goals everyday.

Hope my profile will meet your requirements, I am a native French Speaker but I also speak English, Arabic and Spanish. I am prepared to exceed expectations in this role.
Thank you very much for your time and I look forward to meeting you to discuss the skills I can bring to your team.

Sincerely,
Yasmina Gueznay
